column5: This is the Great White North Glen, we don't even close our windows up here till the temps drop below zero and winter storms are nuthin more than an inconvenience that sometimes slow down the boat ramps

Now no talking about winter Dog we are looking at a warm thanksgiving weekend high 60's now I know thats cold for you but we like those temps in October.Winter is a dirty 6 letter word you can talk about it in November but not October
You're ALWAYS working on your tan    then you have the nerve to flaunt it at us
You said WINTER and everyone is looking for the Icefishing equipment!
I was walking through Sears yesterday and saw a guy setting up a Christmas Tree... I can't repeat what I said to him... at least not here! HH
Was it not Merry Christmas HH

yee haww...bring it on   , I can't wait..I actually headed out in the hopes of catching a steelie today for a bit....it was actually too nice out   water is still too warm for the good fishin  , I am with Lew as well...a minor slow up at the boat ramps
Note: put two shovels in the truck. The ramp will get cleared faster if your partner has a shovel too!
yeaaa bring on winter...im tired of this warm weather
